When I first came here,

137
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,290
he heard I came from Daichuan

138
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:38,580
and was fond of my hometown's green tea.

139
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:40,840
He said

140
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,670
he would pick dew

141
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,040
from the tree to make tea for me.

142
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:55,160
Since then,

143
00:09:57,890 --> 00:09:59,310
the tea I drank every day

144
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:04,030
was prepared by his servants.

145
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:06,850
He also said

146
00:10:08,430 --> 00:10:09,690
he would add some honey

147
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,160
to the tea for me

148
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,240
because it's Xinchuan's way

149
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:17,600
of drinking tea.

150
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:20,800
Later I found out

151
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:25,150
Xinchuan people don't add honey to tea at all.

152
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,020
But I thought

153
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,670
he just hoped

154
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,010
to make my tea

155
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,160
taste more sweet

156
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:40,040
and that was why

157
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,290
